This paper is about semantic parsing, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) that involves converting natural language queries into structured logical forms. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which is focused on NLP and related areas. 

The paper also uses dual learning, which is a machine learning technique that involves training two models simultaneously to improve performance. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

Additionally, the paper proposes a novel reward signal to generate complete and reasonable logical forms, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as these areas often involve developing algorithms to generate relevant and useful outputs.
